text: Jüri Tarmak (21 July 1946 – 22 June 2022) was an Estonian high jumper. He competed for the Soviet Union. He won a gold medal at the 1972 Summer Olympics. Tarmak died on 22 June 2022 in Tallinn, Estonia at the age of 75.Suri olümpiavõitja Jüri Tarmak ==References== Category:1946 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Olympians for Estonia Category:Olympic gold medalists Category:Sportspeople from Tallinn
